File: Duduzane Zuma at his culpable homicide case trial at the Randburg magistrate's court. JOHANNESBURG - Duduzane Zuma is set to learn his fate on Friday in the Randburg magistrate's court. Zuma is facing culpable homicide and reckless and negligent driving charges. READ: Duduzane Zuma judgment expected in July The case relates to a February 2014 car crash on the M1 highway in Gauteng. A woman died after Zuma's Porsche smashed into the minibus taxi she was travelling in. READ: He didn't want Duduzane Zuma to be victimised, witness tells court The former president’s son pleaded not guilty to the charges. Rights group AfriForum is representing the woman's family.